{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a0825774-add6-43c4-b9ad-bace4e85b2ab","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2**, the recommended pattern is:\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor parameter** (not the legacy static property)\n- **Sync init** — use the **constructor**\n- **Async init** — use **`[TestInitialize]`** with `async Task`\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Constructor: sync init + TestContext injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Constructor injection replaced the old `public static TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` pattern in MSTest v3+.\n- `[TestInitialize]` runs before each test and supports `async Task`.\n- For **one-time** class-level async setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` on a `static async Task` method.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"be4be2d0-1ca1-4a4e-9c86-bdf58acf6338","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) instead of the old static property pattern.\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor.\n3. **Asynchronous init**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` method.\n\nLet me provide a clear, concise answer.","outputTokens":450,"requestId":"5C30:B7F6F:24AA3F:2DA6D7:69F5535A"},"id":"f4c740e1-3aac-4a65-b52d-7b77e72e45cf","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:29:11.254Z","parentId":"a794c7e3-f110-408e-9956-0c8e31b2ccb8"}
